WEBVTT

00:01.119 --> 00:02.639
<i> Previously on Broadchurch...</i>

00:02.639 --> 00:04.119
Who did this to me?

00:08.360 --> 00:10.480
Bloody hell, Miller - the sock
found on the Axehampton estate

00:10.479 --> 00:12.159
confirmed as a match
for Trish's DNA.

00:12.159 --> 00:14.199
-So it was used as a gag?
-More than that.

00:14.200 --> 00:16.800
There are traces of one of
our men's DNA on the sock.

00:16.800 --> 00:17.800
Who?

00:23.400 --> 00:25.080
(PHONE RINGS)

00:25.079 --> 00:27.439
-MILLER: It's Katie.
-No, no, no. Not a good idea.

00:27.479 --> 00:30.279
-Why would she call
at this time of night?
-Do not answer it.

00:30.280 --> 00:31.680
-Katie?
-God's sake, Miller.

00:31.680 --> 00:33.600
Can you get to Flintcombe
Farm Shop urgently?

00:33.600 --> 00:36.080
-We're heading somewhere else.
-I think we've found the twine

00:36.079 --> 00:38.319
that was used to tie up
Trish Winterman.

00:38.319 --> 00:39.839
-Stop the car.
-No!

00:39.839 --> 00:41.639
Stop the bloody car!

00:41.639 --> 00:43.519
It's just stuff that
got left in the cab.

00:43.519 --> 00:46.759
-Why haven't you given it back?
-I didn't know whose it was.

00:46.800 --> 00:50.000
A woman has been raped
and you've got her keys.

00:50.000 --> 00:51.800
Not just hers - loads of people's.

00:51.800 --> 00:55.400
-Get out!
-You don't tell me what
I can or can't do anymore.

00:57.560 --> 01:01.120
-Evening, Clive.
-What are you doing here?

01:01.119 --> 01:02.959
Clive Lucas, I'm arresting you

01:02.959 --> 01:04.799
in connection with the
rape of Patricia Winterman

01:04.800 --> 01:07.120
committed at Axehampton House
on Saturday, 28 May this year.

01:07.119 --> 01:09.839
You do not have to say anything,
but it may harm your defence

01:09.839 --> 01:11.279
if you do not mention,
when questioned,

01:11.280 --> 01:13.200
something which you
later rely on in court.

01:13.200 --> 01:15.080
Anything you do say
may be given in evidence.

01:15.079 --> 01:16.919
You understand?

01:16.920 --> 01:18.480
You'll want these as well.

01:18.479 --> 01:22.039
-LUCAS: I can explain.
-Looks like you'll need to.

01:24.959 --> 01:27.119
-What's going on?
-Go back to bed, Michael.

01:27.119 --> 01:28.999
-Where are you taking him?
-Nothing to worry about.

01:29.000 --> 01:31.440
-Why are they taking him?
-It's gonna be fine.

01:32.560 --> 01:34.480
-Everything's gonna be fine.
-(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

01:34.479 --> 01:37.719
ED: I was doing some work
and I came across this bag.

01:37.720 --> 01:40.040
Did you touch it?

01:40.039 --> 01:42.119
When I found it, yeah.

01:42.119 --> 01:44.239
I thought it was something
a customer maybe dropped.

01:44.239 --> 01:46.359
Makes no sense it was out here.

01:46.360 --> 01:49.040
What about the twine -
did you touch that?

01:50.360 --> 01:52.480
Yeah, I pulled it out to see.

01:52.479 --> 01:54.559
-Why?
-I didn't know what it was, did I?

01:54.560 --> 01:57.640
It wasn't till I saw the
twine that I called you.

01:57.639 --> 01:59.079
And then I called you.

01:59.079 --> 02:00.839
Right, so your prints and your DNA

02:00.839 --> 02:02.839
are all over the bag and the twine.

02:02.839 --> 02:05.079
I guess so.

02:05.079 --> 02:07.519
You do have CCTV here,
though, don't you?

02:07.519 --> 02:09.199
Yeah.

02:09.199 --> 02:11.680
OK. Will you go with
the officer, please?

02:17.319 --> 02:19.319
Do you think he's telling the truth?

02:20.360 --> 02:22.080
Honestly, I don't know anymore.

02:28.000 --> 02:30.200
-(SIGHS)
-(FOOTSTEPS)

02:31.519 --> 02:33.399
You alright?

02:34.519 --> 02:36.279
Yeah. Yeah.

02:37.560 --> 02:39.600
You know, you really
can have Chlo's room.

02:39.600 --> 02:42.640
No, I'm not having her
sleeping on the sofa.

02:42.639 --> 02:44.039
You just got out of hospital.

02:44.039 --> 02:46.359
It's fuss over nothing.

02:48.720 --> 02:50.320
Not really.

02:54.079 --> 02:55.799
Didn't expect to see you awake.

02:55.800 --> 02:58.560
I couldn't sleep. I was
worried about you down here.

03:00.439 --> 03:03.519
Thought I'd pretend I was coming
down for a glass of water.

03:05.000 --> 03:06.760
Always were a terrible liar.

03:06.759 --> 03:08.759
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

03:12.360 --> 03:14.360
If neither of us is sleeping,

03:14.360 --> 03:16.600
should I go and make
us a hot chocolate?

03:17.639 --> 03:19.479
Yeah.

