03:32.360 --> 03:34.840
-HARDY: He just found them?
-It's what he said.

03:34.839 --> 03:36.239
And he has a convenient excuse

03:36.239 --> 03:37.799
for his DNA being
all over the evidence.

03:37.800 --> 03:39.880
The thing is we searched
his house, all around there,

03:39.879 --> 03:43.159
including that shed, 40 hours
ago, and we didn't spot that.

03:43.159 --> 03:45.319
And that whole area's
covered by CCTV.

03:45.319 --> 03:47.159
He knows that.
So why would he lie?

03:47.159 --> 03:50.639
Vice is tightening, Miller.
They're starting to squeak.

03:50.639 --> 03:53.679
So Jim Atwood, Clive Lucas
or Ed Burnett - take your pick.

03:53.680 --> 03:55.320
Who do we talk to first?

03:55.319 --> 04:00.159
For the tape, I am showing
Mr Lucas Exhibit AH141.

04:00.159 --> 04:02.959
Why have you got a set
of Trish Winterman's house keys?

04:03.839 --> 04:05.599
She left them in the taxi.

04:07.759 --> 04:10.199
But you didn't think
to give them back to her.

04:10.200 --> 04:12.280
I didn't get round to it.

04:12.280 --> 04:14.520
HARDY: Like you didn't
get round to giving back

04:14.519 --> 04:17.199
all the others you had
locked in your garage drawer.

04:18.079 --> 04:20.559
I didn't know where they lived.

04:20.560 --> 04:22.079
You drove most of them home.

04:22.079 --> 04:24.159
Your company keeps  records of bookings.

04:24.159 --> 04:26.599
Some of them, presumably,
were regular customers.

04:28.879 --> 04:32.759
You see, it looks to me
like a trophy drawer.

04:34.639 --> 04:36.199
Or a collection.

04:40.400 --> 04:43.320
-What did you do with them?
-Nothing.

04:43.319 --> 04:47.199
I...I'm just...cleaning up.

04:47.239 --> 04:49.559
It's not my fault
if people are careless.

04:52.239 --> 04:55.679
Did none of them ever ask
if you'd found their keys?

05:00.920 --> 05:03.440
What was it?
Was it the power?

05:03.439 --> 05:05.639
Knowing you have them...

05:07.519 --> 05:09.199
..knowing you could
use them if you wanted.

05:09.200 --> 05:10.800
Have you ever used any of them?

05:10.800 --> 05:14.160
Let yourself into someone's house?

05:14.159 --> 05:16.279
I'm not that sort of man.

05:16.280 --> 05:19.680
Oh, well...I think you are.

05:19.680 --> 05:23.320
I think your relationship
to real life is a bit troubling.

05:23.319 --> 05:26.439
Where do you get off with
all this having a go at me?

05:26.479 --> 05:29.599
You asked Jim Atwood why he was
arguing with Trish at the party?

05:29.600 --> 05:31.880
Hey?

05:31.879 --> 05:34.759
Have you?

05:34.759 --> 05:37.439
No, we weren't aware of that.
What time was that?

05:37.439 --> 05:39.879
10-ish, I suppose.

05:39.879 --> 05:41.559
She told him to stay away from her.

05:41.560 --> 05:42.800
(FLICKS THROUGH PAPERS)

05:42.800 --> 05:44.200
I don't know why you keep coming

05:44.200 --> 05:45.600
for me when he's out there.

05:45.600 --> 05:48.080
Mmm. You weren't there at that time.

05:50.280 --> 05:52.600
According to the
statement you gave us,

05:52.600 --> 05:55.480
you were on the road to
Lyme with a passenger.

05:58.239 --> 05:59.679
Right.

05:59.680 --> 06:01.720
I might have got confused.

06:01.720 --> 06:03.760
Well, let's clear up that confusion.

06:03.759 --> 06:05.879
What was it?

06:05.879 --> 06:07.359
At the party looking at Jim and Trish

06:07.360 --> 06:09.320
or on the road to Lyme
with a passenger?

06:13.680 --> 06:15.200
Party.

06:16.079 --> 06:18.559
So your previous alibi was false.

06:18.560 --> 06:20.240
You lied to us.

06:20.239 --> 06:22.199
-Not deliberately.
-Oh, it was an accidental lie?

06:22.200 --> 06:24.240
I...I just got my timings muddled.

06:24.239 --> 06:26.799
-Were you alone when you
saw Trish and Jim arguing?
-Yeah.

06:26.839 --> 06:29.559
-Were you on your own for
the rest of the evening?
-Yeah.

06:29.560 --> 06:31.640
So you have no alibi

06:31.639 --> 06:35.199
that can confirm where you were
when the rape was taking place?

06:36.159 --> 06:39.239
No, right...
That's not what I said.

06:39.239 --> 06:43.279
For the tape, I am now
showing Mr Lucas AH127.

06:43.280 --> 06:45.280
Have you ever worn a sock like that?

06:45.280 --> 06:48.480
Those are the socks we
wear to play football,

06:48.479 --> 06:50.159
so, yeah.

06:50.159 --> 06:53.159
That was recovered from the
grounds of Axehampton House.

06:53.200 --> 06:56.200
We found traces of
Trish Winterman's saliva on it,

06:56.200 --> 06:59.560
so we believe that was used
to gag her while she was raped.

06:59.560 --> 07:03.560
And when we tested it,
it came back as a match

07:03.560 --> 07:05.200
with your DNA.

07:07.479 --> 07:09.359
It...it's not mine!

07:09.360 --> 07:11.200
MILLER: We know that you and Trish

07:11.200 --> 07:13.240
previously went for a drink
and she knocked you back.

07:13.239 --> 07:14.879
You have a set of her house keys.

07:14.879 --> 07:17.359
You don't now have an alibi
for the time of the attack

07:17.360 --> 07:19.320
and your DNA is on that sock.

07:19.319 --> 07:21.799
So we need your explanation
as to how this all makes sense

07:21.800 --> 07:23.760
if you didn't rape Trish Winterman.

07:23.759 --> 07:26.159
(STAMMERS) I can't.

07:27.239 --> 07:28.599
Sorry.

07:29.639 --> 07:31.359
I can't explain that.

07:32.439 --> 07:34.879
I still enjoy those moments
when some cocky bastard

07:34.879 --> 07:36.559
trashes their own alibi
without realising it.

07:36.560 --> 07:39.240
We got the CCTV from the farm shop yet?

07:39.239 --> 07:42.199
20 minutes, Nish said.

07:42.200 --> 07:45.080
Right, come on, let's get
in and rattle his cage.

07:45.079 --> 07:46.999
You searched the whole
place two days ago.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.680
That bag wasn't there.

07:48.680 --> 07:51.920
You want us to believe
you see a suspicious bag

07:51.920 --> 07:53.720
inside one of your sheds,

07:53.759 --> 07:56.479
pick it up, leaving
your fingerprints and DNA,

07:56.479 --> 07:57.959
scratch around inside.

07:57.959 --> 08:01.079
"Oh, some blood-stained twine.
I'll fiddle with that too."

08:01.079 --> 08:02.799
I didn't realise
it was a suspicious bag

08:02.800 --> 08:04.320
until I looked inside.

08:04.319 --> 08:06.799
If I did this,
why would I call it in?

08:06.800 --> 08:09.840
It doesn't make any sense.
How stupid would I have to be?

08:09.839 --> 08:11.959
Not stupid, maybe. Desperate.

08:12.839 --> 08:15.719
Check the CCTV, please.

08:15.720 --> 08:17.720
I want to help.

08:17.720 --> 08:19.400
I'm trying to help.

08:20.720 --> 08:22.160
If you waste time on me,

08:22.159 --> 08:23.759
you won't catch the bloke who did it.

08:23.759 --> 08:27.559
I have sat across from you
during all these interviews.

08:27.560 --> 08:30.960
I've listened to every word,
watched your reactions,

08:30.959 --> 08:32.719
I've studied your body language.

08:34.280 --> 08:36.120
And I think there is still something

08:36.119 --> 08:37.599
that you are not telling us.

08:39.239 --> 08:42.399
I don't think you've been
100% honest with us

08:42.400 --> 08:45.480
and I cannot for the life of me
understand why that is.

08:45.479 --> 08:49.879
If you know anything that will
help us rule you out, tell us.

08:49.879 --> 08:52.999
Anything else that happened
that night doesn't matter.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.040
It does matter.

08:59.639 --> 09:01.519
It matters to me.

09:01.519 --> 09:03.599
Why?

09:07.000 --> 09:08.640
Because I heard it.

09:11.400 --> 09:13.480
You heard what, Ed?

09:16.959 --> 09:19.039
I heard her being raped.

09:21.280 --> 09:24.080
I didn't know that's what it was.

09:24.079 --> 09:25.879
I was at the edge of the woods.

09:25.879 --> 09:27.719
This was after I fell.

09:29.400 --> 09:32.520
I heard some sounds coming
from around the waterfall.

09:35.720 --> 09:37.840
I thought it was just drunk sex.

09:37.839 --> 09:41.159
Didn't realise what it was until later,

09:41.159 --> 09:43.079
till I found out what really happened.

09:43.079 --> 09:45.919
I could have stopped it.

09:45.920 --> 09:48.200
I could have helped her.

09:51.479 --> 09:54.519
You wanna know why I've slept
near her place ever since?

09:57.720 --> 10:00.320
Because I failed her.

10:04.280 --> 10:06.720
(SIGHS) Nights like this,
I wish I still smoked.

10:06.759 --> 10:09.519
-I KNEW you used to smoke!
-What's your instinct?

10:09.519 --> 10:11.159
You think that's finally
the truth from him?

10:11.159 --> 10:12.919
Well, it could be, or it could be

10:12.920 --> 10:14.800
a very clever
get-out-of-jail-free card.

10:14.800 --> 10:16.440
"I wasn't there, but I was nearby."

10:16.439 --> 10:18.799
If that's what he's been
carrying, that explains a lot.

10:18.800 --> 10:20.440
That's a thing to live with.

10:20.439 --> 10:22.639
Well, it's nothing compared
to what Trish is dealing with.

10:22.639 --> 10:24.239
-(PHONE BUZZES)
-No.

10:25.079 --> 10:27.239
Oh, we've got the shop CCTV.

10:27.239 --> 10:29.399
This footage is timecoded,

10:29.400 --> 10:31.280
and when this happened,
Ed was in custody.

10:31.280 --> 10:32.960
So, what, Ed's in the clear?

10:32.959 --> 10:35.319
What do you reckon - Lucas or Jim?

10:35.319 --> 10:37.119
It's the right sort of build.

10:37.119 --> 10:39.119
So he ran in here. Building's here.

10:39.119 --> 10:42.079
And then he runs out here,
towards this field.

10:43.720 --> 10:45.880
Ah!

10:45.879 --> 10:48.119
HARDY: What are you doing?

10:50.479 --> 10:53.239
Yes, there - the figure on the CCTV

10:53.239 --> 10:55.839
runs into a field on the
edge of Flintcombe Farm

10:55.839 --> 10:58.399
with a public footpath through it.

10:58.400 --> 11:00.840
You go down that footpath
and it leads to this road here,

11:00.839 --> 11:02.199
which means...

11:09.720 --> 11:12.520
-Got it!
-Go on.

11:12.519 --> 11:15.319
So this field links to that road,

11:15.319 --> 11:18.719
which has a parking lay-by and a
newly installed traffic camera.

11:18.720 --> 11:22.440
(TYPES)

11:22.439 --> 11:26.399
There he is. There's his car
and there's his registration.

11:26.439 --> 11:29.479
Very good, Miller!
You should do this for a living.

11:29.479 --> 11:31.759
And that licence plate belongs to...

11:39.079 --> 11:41.119
Swaggery little shit.

11:45.959 --> 11:48.599
MARK: Do you remember when we
came and looked at this house?

11:50.159 --> 11:52.519
You walked straight into that kitchen,

11:52.519 --> 11:54.359
looked out the window and you said,

11:54.400 --> 11:56.240
"Imagine being able to
live somewhere like this.

11:56.239 --> 11:58.159
"Imagine having that
view every morning."

11:58.159 --> 12:00.999
And I knew then that was...

12:02.159 --> 12:04.079
That was it. Decision made.

12:04.079 --> 12:06.239
I was right, though, wasn't I?

12:06.239 --> 12:08.319
You were always right.

12:08.319 --> 12:10.279
About pretty much everything.

12:10.280 --> 12:13.360
Not everything, but pretty much.

12:14.239 --> 12:16.359
I'm just catching up half the time.

12:16.360 --> 12:20.000
A few months later,
I'm like, "Oh, yeah. Yeah.

12:20.000 --> 12:22.320
"What Beth said was right."

12:25.800 --> 12:28.800
That's what it's like being me.

12:28.800 --> 12:32.080
"A month late and 10 quid
short," my mum would have said.

12:32.079 --> 12:34.239
You're not that bad.

12:34.239 --> 12:36.679
Oh. Thanks very much.

12:36.680 --> 12:38.760
Make a good hot chocolate.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.560
Yeah, my kitchen skills are alright.

12:49.079 --> 12:51.039
Did you not want to live?

12:56.879 --> 12:58.559
No.

13:01.400 --> 13:02.760
What about us?

13:04.720 --> 13:07.760
Me and...Chlo and Lizzie?

13:11.000 --> 13:13.080
I don't feel part of you anymore.

13:16.479 --> 13:18.479
I don't live here.

13:18.479 --> 13:20.119
We're not together.

13:22.360 --> 13:24.560
We're not gonna be, are we?

13:27.639 --> 13:30.199
Come on, least you can do
is be honest with me.

13:33.959 --> 13:35.479
No.

13:38.439 --> 13:41.519
I don't think we can be together.

13:41.519 --> 13:43.559
Not right now.

13:44.839 --> 13:46.359
Yeah.

13:48.839 --> 13:50.359
Yeah.

13:58.280 --> 14:00.320
I really love you, Mark.

14:02.439 --> 14:04.399
I always have.

14:04.400 --> 14:06.480
So much.

14:07.400 --> 14:09.920
I remember when I used
to see you and I...

14:09.920 --> 14:13.480
..I felt like my body was bursting.

14:15.680 --> 14:17.680
Not...not now?

14:18.720 --> 14:20.440
No.

14:22.360 --> 14:23.720
We just...

14:26.959 --> 14:28.999
We went different ways.

14:29.000 --> 14:31.320
I don't even know when.

14:33.400 --> 14:35.000
Because of Dan?

14:35.920 --> 14:38.800
No. Before. You know that.

14:42.319 --> 14:44.399
You can still see Lizzie.

14:45.639 --> 14:48.839
You know, we can be friends.

14:48.839 --> 14:50.399
You can come to the house.

14:50.400 --> 14:52.080
No, no.

14:52.079 --> 14:55.119
I...I have to go.

14:55.119 --> 14:59.679
I have to...sort myself out for a bit.

14:59.680 --> 15:01.400
For a while.

15:03.560 --> 15:06.360
It's too difficult
being near, you know?

15:06.360 --> 15:08.640
And I think that's what's done me in.

15:17.319 --> 15:20.199
Seeing you and the girls and...

15:22.439 --> 15:24.799
..this house, all of the memories...

15:24.800 --> 15:29.600
..you know, it's...it's what
I struggle with, I think.

15:33.360 --> 15:36.200
I'll be alright, though.
I'll be alright.

15:36.200 --> 15:38.480
I just...just need to
put myself back together.

15:40.079 --> 15:43.119
Away from here, you know?
Anywhere.

15:49.759 --> 15:51.599
So this is how it happens, then?

15:57.839 --> 15:59.799
I love you.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.560
Yeah, I love you too.

16:18.239 --> 16:20.399
MILLER: We've got
Leo Humphries on camera

16:20.400 --> 16:23.240
disposing of a bag
containing blood-stained twine

16:23.239 --> 16:26.999
which Forensics have confirmed
is a match with the fibres

16:27.000 --> 16:28.680
taken from Trish Winterman's wrists.

16:28.680 --> 16:30.680
But we also have Lucas in custody,

16:30.680 --> 16:32.880
no alibi, and his DNA on the gag.

16:32.879 --> 16:35.239
Maybe it was both of them together.

16:35.280 --> 16:38.200
So Leo disposing of the bag for Lucas

16:38.200 --> 16:40.080
to throw suspicion onto Ed?

16:40.079 --> 16:42.759
Do they even know each other?
Is there a connection?

16:43.959 --> 16:46.599
Yeah. Football, uh... football sock.

16:46.600 --> 16:48.760
Leo and Lucas both brought
the goals to the match

16:48.759 --> 16:50.159
with that same blue twine.

16:50.159 --> 16:52.679
Someone said Leo trains the team

16:52.680 --> 16:55.440
and Lucas is on that team,
so, yeah, there's a connection.

16:55.439 --> 16:57.999
(DOORBELL RINGS)

16:58.000 --> 17:00.440
Hi, Danielle. Is Leo here?

17:00.439 --> 17:02.839
-No, he's not, sorry.
-We went to his house.

17:02.839 --> 17:04.638
-His dad said he was here.
-(PHONE RINGS)

17:04.638 --> 17:06.759
And if he's not here,
why is his phone ringing?

17:07.959 --> 17:09.719
Come on out, Leo.

17:13.800 --> 17:16.440
We have arrested Leo Humphries

17:16.439 --> 17:19.519
